    abstract = {A general formula for global gauge and gravitational anomalies is derived. It is used to show that the anomaly free supergravity and superstring theories in ten dimensions are all free of global anomalies that might have ruined their consistency. However, it is shown that global anomalies lead to some restrictions on allowed compactifϊcations of these theories. For example, in the case of O(32) superstring theory, it is shown that a global anomaly related to π7(O(32)) leads to a Dirac-like quantization condition for the field strength of the antisymmetric tensor field.},
