    abstract = {This paper (Part I) and the sequel (Part II) prove the existence of a smooth, non-trivial, finite action solution to the SU(2) Yang-Mills-Higgs equations on 1R3 in the BogomoΓnyi-Prasad-Sommerfield limit. The proof uses a simple form of Morse theory known as Ljusternik-Snirelman theory. Part I establishes that a form of Lusternik-Snirelman theory is applicable to the SU (2) Yang-Mills-Higgs equations. Here, a sufficient condition for the existence of the aforementioned solution is derived. Part II contains the completed existence proof. There it is demonstrated that the sufficient condition of Part I is satisfied by the SU(2) Yang-Mills-Higgs equations.},
